      "source": [
        "---\n",
        "title: \"Tokenization, Embeddings, Padding, and Masking\"\n",
        "subtitle: \"Sequence Processing in Deep Learning\"\n",
        "author: \"Miguel Fonseca\"\n",
        "format:\n",
        "  revealjs:\n",
        "    toc: true\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "# Motivation\n",
        "\n",
        "## Why Text Needs Processing\n",
        "\n",
        "- Models operate on **numbers, not text**\n",
        "- Raw text is:\n",
        "  - Variable length\n",
        "  - Discrete\n",
        "  - Unstructured\n",
        "\n",
        ">Goal: transform text → structured numerical tensors\n",
        "\n",
        "### Pipeline\n",
        "\n",
        "Raw Text → Tokenization → Integer Sequences → Padding → Embedding → Model\n",
        "\n",
        "# Tokenization\n",
        "\n",
        "## What is Tokenization?\n",
        "\n",
        "- Splitting text into units:\n",
        "  - Words\n",
        "  - Subwords\n",
        "  - Characters\n",
        "\n",
        ">Example: \"Deep learning is powerful\" → [\"deep\", \"learning\", \"is\", \"powerful\"]\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "## Types of Tokenization\n",
        "\n",
        "- **Word-level**\n",
        "    - ```\"deep learning is fun\" → [\"deep\", \"learning\", \"is\", \"fun\"]```\n",
        "\n",
        "- **Subword (BPE / WordPiece)**\n",
        "    - ```\"unbelievable\" → [\"un\", \"believ\", \"able\"]```\n",
        "    - ```\"playing\" → [\"play\", \"##ing\"]```   (WordPiece style)\n",
        "- **Character-level**\n",
        "    - ```\"cat\" → [\"c\", \"a\", \"t\"]```\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "## Tokenization in TensorFlow"
      ],
      "id": "ac16a0e2"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "from tensorflow.keras.preprocessing.text import Tokenizer\n",
        "\n",
        "texts = [\n",
        "    \"deep learning is powerful\",\n",
        "    \"machine learning is fun\"\n",
        "]\n",
        "\n",
        "tokenizer = Tokenizer(num_words=1000, oov_token=\"<OOV>\")\n",
        "tokenizer.fit_on_texts(texts)\n",
        "\n",
        "sequences = tokenizer.texts_to_sequences(texts)\n",
        "\n",
        "print(sequences)"
      ],
      "id": "a61ad6f7",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "**Vocabulary Mapping**"
      ],
      "id": "a7ae6115"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "print(tokenizer.word_index)"
      ],
      "id": "282964d5",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "**Problem: Variable-Length Sequences**\n",
        "\n",
        "```\n",
        "[3, 1, 2, 5]\n",
        "[4, 1, 2, 6]\n",
        "[3, 1]\n",
        "```\n",
        "\n",
        "# Padding\n",
        "\n",
        "## Padding: Why Do We Need It?\n",
        "\n",
        "### Problem: Variable-Length Sequences\n",
        "\n",
        "Text sequences have different lengths:\n",
        "\n",
        "`[3, 1, 2, 5]`\n",
        "\n",
        "`[4, 1]`\n",
        "\n",
        "Neural networks require:\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\n",
        "(\\text{batch}, \\text{fixed length})\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n",
        "> Cannot stack sequences directly into tensors\n",
        "\n",
        "### Solution: Padding\n",
        "\n",
        "Add special token (0) to standardize length:\n",
        "\n",
        "[4, 1] → [4, 1, 0, 0]\n",
        "\n",
        ":::{.callout-tip title=\"Key Idea\"}\n",
        "Padding = making data rectangular\n",
        ":::\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "## Padding Sequences"
      ],
      "id": "4aea2fd6"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "from tensorflow.keras.preprocessing.sequence import pad_sequences\n",
        "\n",
        "padded = pad_sequences(sequences, padding='post')\n",
        "print(padded)"
      ],
      "id": "ab5b20d1",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "## Padding: Subtleties & Consequences\n",
        "\n",
        "**Types of Padding**\n",
        "\n",
        "- Post-padding (preferred in NLP)\n",
        "    - `[real data | padding]`\n",
        "- Pre-padding\n",
        "    - `[padding | real data]`\n",
        "\n",
        "**Hidden Problem**\n",
        "\n",
        "Padding introduces fake data (zeros)\n",
        "\n",
        ":::{.callout-warning}\n",
        "Model may learn: *“zero is important”*.\n",
        ":::\n",
        "\n",
        "**Implication**\n",
        "\n",
        "Padding must be handled carefully\n",
        "\n",
        "- Leads to masking\n",
        "\n",
        "# Embeddings\n",
        "\n",
        "## Embeddings\n",
        "\n",
        "- Dense vector representation of tokens\n",
        "- Captures semantic meaning\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "## Embeddings: From Tokens to Vectors\n",
        "\n",
        "### Core Idea\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\n",
        "w \\rightarrow \\mathbf{e}_w \\in \\mathbb{R}^d\n",
        "$$​\n",
        "\n",
        "### Embedding Matrix\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\\mathbf{E} \\in \\mathbb{R}^{V \\times d}\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n",
        "- $V$: vocabulary size\n",
        "- $d$: embedding dimension\n",
        "\n",
        "**Lookup**\n",
        "\n",
        "- Input:  `[3, 1, 2]`\n",
        "- Output: `[E[3], E[1], E[2]]`\n",
        "\n",
        "> Trainable lookup table\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "## Why Embeddings Work\n",
        "\n",
        "### Semantic Geometry\n",
        "\n",
        "Similar words → close vectors\n",
        "\n",
        ":::{.callout title=\"Example\"}\n",
        "king - man + woman ≈ queen\n",
        ":::\n",
        "\n",
        "### vs One-Hot Encoding\n",
        "\n",
        "| One-hot    | Embedding        |\n",
        "| ---------- | ---------------- |\n",
        "| Sparse     | Dense            |\n",
        "| No meaning | Semantic meaning |\n",
        "\n",
        "### Training\n",
        "\n",
        "- Learned via backpropagation\n",
        "- Only used rows are updated\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "## Embedding Layer"
      ],
      "id": "df1aad38"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "from tensorflow.keras.layers import Embedding\n",
        "\n",
        "embedding_layer = Embedding(input_dim=1000, output_dim=16)"
      ],
      "id": "91543a3a",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "# Pipeline\n",
        "\n",
        "## Putting It Together\n",
        "\n",
        "**Text**\n",
        "\n",
        "1. Tokenization\n",
        "1. Integer sequences\n",
        "1. Padding\n",
        "1. Embedding\n",
        "1. Model\n",
        "\n",
        "**Tensor Shapes**\n",
        "\n",
        "`(batch, seq_len) → (batch, seq_len, embedding_dim)`\n",
        "\n",
        "### Intuition\n",
        "\n",
        "- Padding → structure\n",
        "- Embedding → meaning\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "## Full Pipeline Example"
      ],
      "id": "fccfff0b"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "import tensorflow as tf\n",
        "\n",
        "model = tf.keras.Sequential([\n",
        "    tf.keras.layers.Embedding(1000, 16, input_length=10),\n",
        "    tf.keras.layers.GlobalAveragePooling1D(),\n",
        "    tf.keras.layers.Dense(16, activation='relu'),\n",
        "    tf.keras.layers.Dense(1, activation='sigmoid')\n",
        "])\n",
        "\n",
        "model.summary()"
      ],
      "id": "5cdbe3f3",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "# Masking\n",
        "\n",
        "## Masking: Ignoring Fake Data\n",
        "\n",
        "### Problem\n",
        "\n",
        "Padding introduces noise:\n",
        "\n",
        "`[3, 1, 0, 0]`\n",
        "\n",
        ">Model should ignore zeros\n",
        "\n",
        "### Solution: Masking\n",
        "\n",
        "Mask tensor:\n",
        "\n",
        "`[1, 1, 0, 0]`\n",
        "\n",
        "- 1 → real data\n",
        "- 0 → ignore\n",
        "\n",
        "**TensorFlow Example**"
      ],
      "id": "b8e4a943"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "embedding = tf.keras.layers.Embedding(\n",
        "    input_dim=10000,\n",
        "    output_dim=64,\n",
        "    mask_zero=True\n",
        ")"
      ],
      "id": "f1456218",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "## Masking: Special Cases\n",
        "\n",
        "Where It Works:\n",
        "\n",
        "- LSTM / GRU\n",
        "- RNNs\n",
        "- Attention layers\n",
        "\n",
        ":::{.callout-important title=\"Time Series\"}\n",
        "In time series, masking is not limited to zero values.\n",
        "\n",
        "Missing data may be encoded as:\n",
        "\n",
        "- `NaN`\n",
        "- `-1`\n",
        "- sentinel values (e.g., `-999`)\n",
        "- domain-specific flags\n",
        ":::\n",
        "\n",
        "Mask must be explicitly defined, e.g.:"
      ],
      "id": "c9c48226"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "x = tf.constant([[1, 2, -999], [3, -999, -999]])\n",
        "mask = tf.math.not_equal(x, -999)"
      ],
      "id": "39a01259",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "## Masking in TensorFlow\n",
        "\n",
        "### Masking with RNN - Text"
      ],
      "id": "797d6f78"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "model = tf.keras.Sequential([\n",
        "    tf.keras.layers.Embedding(1000, 16, mask_zero=True),\n",
        "    tf.keras.layers.LSTM(32),\n",
        "    tf.keras.layers.Dense(1)\n",
        "])"
      ],
      "id": "13dadb14",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "### Masking with RNN - Time Series"
      ],
      "id": "e6041ffa"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "import tensorflow as tf\n",
        "\n",
        "model = tf.keras.Sequential([\n",
        "    tf.keras.layers.Masking(mask_value=-999.0),\n",
        "    tf.keras.layers.LSTM(32),\n",
        "    tf.keras.layers.Dense(1)\n",
        "])"
      ],
